metadata.name: Acid Quilt #185
metadata.description:
This is an abstract work. There is no true or correct orientation.

Inspired by repeater patterns, tiles, tessellations, and quilts. Not as goofy as the Collage of Collage set but still some goofiness to it. This collage set is made up of layers sketched on a really old ipad. 

The project does not have a repeater functions built in, just produces the single base unit. My hope is that the output be used on a larger canvas and repeated, tiled, or tessellated. Some outputs might could look good in a quilt. 

These online tools (as of Feb 2022) are easy to use for making tiles. Windows also makes it easy to tile, as does Photoshop:
- https://www.imgonline.com.ua/eng/check-texture-tiling.php
- https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/gdiplus/-gdiplus-tiling-a-shape-with-an-image-use
- https://prinfab.com/printed-fabric?r2=magic

(^This^ is very much not a best practice, including links in this description that might not exist in the future)

There are more than 1.3 billion possible combos!

Please enjoy!

metadata.name: RAUSCH #26
metadata.description:
RAUSCH is a series of generative artworks that explore imaginary digital architectures. 

This series challenges traditional notions of architectural representation and raises important questions about the role of resolution in design. Just as the pixel resolution of an image affects its perceived quality, the resolution of an architectural space can affect its qualities and livability. By embracing digital variation through codes, this series explores the interplay between abstract and concrete space through multiple resolutions. 

RAUSCH is inspired by the feeling of being overwhelmed by complex, chaotic and messy sensations, and aims to engage the viewer through a sense of wonder, disorientation, and awe.

Released on the occasion of Companions of Code, a group exhibition by VerticalCrypto Art at The NFT Gallery in London. 
Curated by Micol Ap. Exhibition 10-24 February 2023

â€¢ '7' Landscape 16:9 - 1920x1080
â€¢ '8' Portrait 9:16 - 1080x1920
â€¢ '9' Square 1:1 - 1024x1024
â€¢ 'DoubleClick' Fullscreen

Save & Export Image:
â€¢ 'S' save a .png of in current resolution

Save & Export GIF:
â€¢ 'G' save a 1-2 sec. seamless loop .gif of current view 
â€¢ 'P' save a 12-24 sec. seamless loop .gif of all the views
â€¢ 'Tâ€™ scale down current resolution, save a 12 sec. seamless loop .gif

Steps to save a gif/png :
â€¢ go in live/open mode (wait)
â€¢ resize canvas with 6,7,8, or 9 to your desired aspect ratio (wait)
â€¢ press S,G or P to save & download (wait) 
â€¢ enjoy RAUSCH :)

Save & Export GIF for social media sharing:
â€¢ go in live/open mode (wait)
â€¢ press T or G wait for recalculation & download. 
â€¢ enjoy RAUSCH 
â€¢ post on Twitter ;)

metadata.name: Learning to Fly #9
metadata.description:
It all started with @chilltulpa saying in fxhash discord "I wish i could make art" and @mknol answering with a few lines of code to create generative art... It was more than enough for me to finally dive in, and try to make something. 

Learning is the key here, learning is being alive.
This is me learning, this is a beginning, I'm learning to fly.

metadata.name: Currency 2.0 #5
metadata.description:
This work is the 2nd part of a series of conceptual artworks on art and valuation. The emergent differential behaviour of the market that may be generated between the currency series is the intended result of the work. 

Each token has an individual value of 1 FXT, has its unique colour. When the token is touched, it glows golden and shows the cumulative value of all the total tokens of the series, that is 100 FXT, and it goes back to it based value of 1FXT when its not being touched.

Each token is 1 tez with 10% royalty (the minimum allowed)

Currency 2.0 @beardcoded
